bq. But I am able to read a dataset which I could not do with adlfs 0.5.5 (I get that error about a list of files instead of a dictionary using fs.find() with the latest version).

[~ldacey] can you open an issue about that at {{adlfs}}? {{find}} is supposed to return a dictionary with {{detail=True}}

(although I am wondering if you are not accidentally using an older version, as from the source code it seems to be returning a dictionary ..)

{quote}
{code}
>>>  fs.info("dev/testing10/evaluations")                               
{'name': 'dev/testing10/evaluations/', 'size': 0, 'type': 'directory'}   
{code}
{quote}

[~ldacey] that looks correct. But so in the same environment as where you get the above result, {{pq.read_table("dev/testing10/evaluations")}} is failing with "FileNotFoundError: dev/testing10/evaluations"?
